Diagram 3 (No Problem?)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Continuing from the previous diagram -
\par
\par When white plays at 1, it is ingenious for black to play at 2, giving white a second stone to eat. Now you may have a good idea of what black is planning.
\par
\par Even though white captures the two black stones with 3 and seems to have no problems, next -
\par }
