Diagram 4 (Double Snapback)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black's throw-in at 1 is the finishing blow. Now, the stones seem to have quite a strange shape.
\par
\par No matter which black stone white captures, whether it be 1 or \'a1\'e3, black's snapback works. Therefore, white's whole group in the corner is captured.
\par
\par This is an incredible double snapback.
\par }
